narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I accidentally answered all of these questions for Intergroup Relations lab, not realizing there were different forms for Jenn and Jack's labs. Apologies! I always appreciate the concrete and thoughtful feedback that I get from my peers (and mentors) during lab.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Lab is a great place to learn from faculty and peers, obtain feedback on research, and get recommendations for further reading. I have one controversial suggestion, which is to explicitly encourage everyone to refrain from doing outside work on their computers during lab. I understand that from time to time people have to finish things urgently, but I also know there are some people who do this every week, which I think detracts from the atmosphere that I otherwise love.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would definitely encourage (and indeed have) others to attend lab!
